My son these b movies. He was thrilled with the set. We have watched them all and actually  enjoyed it

Caught these three on the SyFy channel at one time or another. This set is not all that re-watchable. I don't recommend it unless you have seen them on SyFy and you like them. Blood Monkey: TV Movie 90 min Horror/Sci-Fi/Thriller January 27, 2008 USA Students are taken on a field trip by their professor. The professor (F. Murray Abraham) knows that the monkeys are killers but yet he takes his students in their jungle anyway. This is mediocre B SciFi movie and a disappointment to see F. Murray Abraham lower his standards to this level. Maneaster: TV Movie 88 min Horror/Thriller 2007 USA The town sheriff (Gary Busey) hunts an escaped tiger. A young boy befriends it even though it kills several people. I didn't turn it off, but I don't see this as re-watchable. In the Spider's Web: TV Movie 90 min Horror/Sci-Fi August 26, 2007 USA While a group of students trek through the jungle one is bitten by a spider. They find an American doctor (Lance Henriksen) to help, but they aren't sure if he is really trying to save him or use him in an experiment. Recommendations: Maneater Triple Feature 4: Wyvern / Sand Serpents / Carny CA Luster
